      "writtenOn": "2020-04-07T20:22:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e The redacted case literally returns the string \"\u003credacted\u003e\"\n\nThat’s absolutely worth a comment.\n\nThat’s valuable any time you’re processing data where the values might not be obvious. If you’ve got some code that processes symbol names one at a time, like you do here, and if sometimes the things you see won’t be symbol names but will be something else, then that won’t be obvious to other engineers or even to future Justin unless that’s captured somewhere, like in a comment.",
